APQR Summary
NOTE:
  (1) Overall conclusions must be based on presented data and information.
  (2) Ensure that the Analysis and Conclusions from each section are complete, clear and consistent.
  (3) Make the necessary correlations between sections as appropriate.
  (4) Ensure that all potential issues are appropriately addressed.
 
All data compiled and evaluated during this review period support that the manufacturing processes, control procedures, and specifications for this product have been maintained in an adequate state of control and continue to perform in delivering acceptable product quality. All applicable systems for production and QC testing at this site were maintained in a validated state. Appropriate change control and requalification testing were performed as required. No adverse trends were observed in the Product Overview.
 
There were identified issues with potential product quality impact. The associated corrective actions have been completed and closed per Quality Record.
 
Manufacturing performance for this product was consistent with previous years and no recurring process or control testing events were observed. In addition, the product stability testing data supported the current specifications and storage conditions. However, there were associated ongoing corrective actions which have been initiated - refer to the following.
